article.description: — Tyler Stephenson-Moore scored 23 points as Stony Brook beat Stonehill 81-63 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Stony Brook wins 81-63 against Stonehill
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- — Tyler Stephenson-Moore scored 23 points as Stony Brook beat Stonehill 81-63 on Wednesday night. Stephenson-Moore shot 8 for 13, including 5 for 9 from beyond the arc for the Seawolves (3-5). Jared Frey scored 12 points and added five rebounds and five assists. Keenan Fitzmorris shot 3 of 5 from the field and 5 for 6 from the foul line to finish with 11 points, while adding six rebounds and three blocks. The Skyhawks (1-9) were led in scoring by Tony Felder, who finished with 11 points. Chas Stinson added 10 points and two steals for Stonehill. Se'yphon Triplett also had 10 points and two steals. The loss is the eighth straight for the Skyhawks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
